==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*ἀμήν / amēn / am-ane'

===Etymology===
Of Hebrew origin [[אמן]] {{HH|543}}; properly firm, that is, (figuratively) trustworthy;

===Adverb===
'''ἀμήν'''

# adverbially surely (often as interjection so be it):  [[amen]], [[verily]].

